author: Kyle Porter
title: 2015 Presidents Cup Live Blog: Scores, updates, highlights from day 4
text:
The US will try to win its ninth Presidents Cup in 11 attempts on Sunday in South Korea against the International team. They hold a one-point lead (9.5 to 8.5), but the International team has been hanging tough since getting rolled on the first day. 
There are some pretty fascinating matchups in the 12 singles matches. We'll be live blogging about all of them right here all evening (and morning). Keep it right here for all kinds of commentary (mostly sarcastic) as well as Patrick Reed GIFs. It should be a blast. 



South Korea is ready. (Twitter/PGATour)
